    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-10-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <head>No. 261.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">H. H.
                                Morgan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>,
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-10-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 16, 1884</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 672.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I herewith transmit, for your information, in
                        connection with recent correspondence with your legation, the inclosed copy
                        of a note<note n="*" xml:id="d262fn1">For inclosure see document No. 267 <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note>
                    <pb facs="0480" n="380" xml:id="pg_380"/> from the minister of Mexico here
                        of the 9th instant, stating that his Government renounces its claim to the
                        ownership of Morteritos island, so called, in the Rio Grande, near Roma,
                        Tex.</p>
                <p>In reply to Mr. Romero’s note I have expressed the gratification which this
                        Government felt at this decision, and added that it was only what the
                        President and this Department had good cause to expect from the well-known
                        high sense of justice of the Mexican Government and people.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
